HARDWARE:

Hardware is designed with gEDA suite. All sources are available in 
"<xarias_root>/schematics/" directory.  You can find particular boards 
schematics in "<xarias_root>/schematics/vX.Y/" directories. For details 
of specific board please see "<xarias_root>/schematics/vX.Y/README" file.

WARNING: please take a note, that you should edit 
"<xarias_root>/schematics/vX.Y/gafrc" to point correctly to your
"<xarias_root>/schematics/symbols" directory.


FIRMWARE:

To be able to compile the firmware you have to have installed 
avr-gcc cross-compiler and avr-libc libraries. For more information
please refer to http://www.nongnu.org/avr-libc/
and http://www.avrfreaks.net/wiki/index.php/Documentation:AVR_GCC


For more information please refer to: http://xarias.googlecode.com/
